    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI'll preface this by saying that this isn't a real blocker for me, since there is a workaround, but I thought I would still report it in case it turns out to be a symptom of a more important bug elsewhere.\n\nThere is a classic Vim mapping for selecting open buffers: `nnoremap <leader>b :ls<cr>:b<space>`.\n\nIt runs `:ls`, which list buffers in the pager window, and then immediately insert `:b ` in the command line to select a buffer by number or (tab-completable) name, _while the listing from `:ls` is still visible_.\n\nHowever, it doesn't fully work with `ui2`: the buffer listing is dismissed from view when `:b ` is entered on the command line.\n\nIt _does_ work when using a Lua function for the RHS of the mapping instead:\n\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set(\"n\", \"<leader>b\", function()\n  vim.cmd.ls()\n  vim.fn.feedkeys(\":b \", \"t\")\nend)\n```\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nIn `minimal.lua`:\n\n```lua\nrequire(\"vim._core.ui2\").enable({})\nvim.keymap.set(\"n\", \"<leader>b\", \":ls<cr>:b<space>\")\n```\n\nLoad two buffers:\n\n```\nnvim --clean -u minimal.lua -c next a b\n```\n\nType `\\b`, and notice that the only thing showing is `:b ` in the command line, without the buffers listing being visible.\n\n<img width=\"1125\" height=\"343\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/79350e6a-0970-4ad5-8fba-b8c3aabad6e3\" />\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe list of buffer is visible when using the `:b` command\n\n<img width=\"1123\" height=\"250\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f5f96967-9a51-4e89-8762-45e49247e4c9\" />\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-246+gd393975b04\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nneovim-nightly-bin from AUR",
